OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Michael W. Ferro Jr.Chief Executive Officer, Chairman, and Member of Board of Investors, Merrick Ventures, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 11 Board Members in 11 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships50--
Background

		Mr. Michael W. Ferro, Jr., is the Founder of Merrick Ventures, LLC and serves as its Chairman and Chief Executive Officer. Mr. Ferro serves as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Merrick RIS LLC. He is the Founder of higi SH llc and serves as its Chairman. He was an Investment Professional at Chicago Ventures. He founded Huron Technologies Inc. (alternate name Click Commerce, Inc). in 1996 and served as its Chairman and Chief Executive Officer since 1996. Prior ... to Click Commerce, he founded Chem-Roof in 1988. He served as the President at the Earthwood Care division of Pettibone Corporation from 1992 to 1994. He also serves at Chicagoland Entrepreneurial Center, Investment Arm. He is a Co-Founder of Illinois Innovation Accelerator Fund, L.P. He founded WarrantyCheck.com, Inc. and served as its Chairman. Mr. Ferro is a recognized entrepreneur and technology innovator with a significant track record of leading companies that deliver significant value for shareholders. He worked at Merrick Media, LLC.  He serves as the Chairman of  Chicagoland Entrepreneurial Center and Sun-Times Media, LLC. He has been Non-Executive Chairman at Tronc, Inc since February 4, 2016. He served as Chairman of Wrapports LLC. He served as Non-Executive Chairperson of Merge Healthcare Incorporated from November 21, 2014 to October 13, 2015. Mr. Ferro served as the Chairman of Merge Healthcare Incorporated from June 4, 2008 to August 26, 2013. He serves as Vice Chairman of the World Health Imaging, Telemedicine and Informatics Alliance (WHITIA). He serves as a Director of WarrantyCheck.com Inc. He serves as a Director of Chicago News Cooperative. He serves as a Director with the RAND Health Board of Advisors. He serves as a Board Member of the Economics Club of Chicago and a Director of The Executives’ Club of Chicago. He serves as a Director of The Chicago Museum of Science and Industry, The Field Museum of Chicago, The Joffrey Ballet of Chicago, Northwestern University and the Lyric Opera of Chicago. Mr. Ferro serves on the Boards of Children’s Memorial Hospital, Northwestern Memorial Foundation, The Chicago community trust, Big Shoulders Foundation and After School Matters, Inc. He served as a Director of Stellent, Inc. since July 2001. He served as a Director of Merge Healthcare Incorporated from June 4, 2008 to August 26, 2013. He served as a Director of Click Commerce, Inc. since 1996. He is also a member of Young President’ Organization, World Business Chicago and The Commercial Club of Chicago. In addition to his civic and philanthropic activities, he participates in several business organizations. He has won numerous awards including the 2006 Ernst & Young Entrepreneur of the Year Award in the technology category. Mr. Ferro is credited by many publications as the “Father of the Extranet,” which has served as the underlying technology model for the service-oriented architecture used on the Internet. He was also named a 2006 Henry Crown Fellow by the Aspen Institute. He has received the Chief Executive Officer National Young Entrepreneur of the Year award and the Humanitarian of the Year Award from the Holocaust Memorial Foundation. He has received the KPMG Illinois High-Tech Award and was listed as one of the ‘Top 40 Under 40’ by Crain’s Chicago Business. Mr. Ferro holds a B.A. from the University of Illinois.Read Full Background




